The paper discusses security and privacy challenges in MapReduce on clouds, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper focuses on security and privacy aspects of MapReduce. The second likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as MapReduce is a distributed computing system. The third likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as MapReduce is used for processing large-scale data. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases), as MapReduce is used for data analysis. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering), as the paper discusses existing security and privacy protocols for MapReduce.
